  "prompt": "What are the best schools in Hyderabad for 8th class?",
  "response": "Hyderabad boasts numerous schools renowned for their academic excellence, infrastructure, and holistic development programs. Here\u2019s a list of some of the best schools for 8th class in Hyderabad based on their reputation, facilities, and performance:\n\n### **Top CBSE Schools**\n1. **Delhi Public School (DPS), Hyderabad**  \n   - Known for its strong academic curriculum and extracurricular activities.\n   \n2. **Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan's Public School**  \n   - Offers a balanced focus on academics and co-curricular activities.\n\n3. **Oakridge International School**  \n   - Renowned for its global curriculum and world-class infrastructure.\n\n4. **Sri Chaitanya Techno School**  \n   - Popular for its focus on competitive exams and academic rigor.\n\n---\n\n### **Top ICSE Schools**\n1. **St. Ann\u2019s High School**  \n   - One of the oldest and most reputed schools in Hyderabad.\n\n2. **All Saints\u2019 High School**  \n   - Known for its disciplined environment and strong academic track record.\n\n3. **Johnson Grammar School**  \n   - Offers a comprehensive ICSE curriculum with a focus on holistic education.\n\n4. **Vijaya High School**  \n   - Renowned for its excellent faculty and academic results.\n\n---\n\n### **Top State Board Schools**\n1. **Meridian School**  \n   - Focuses on fostering creativity and critical thinking.\n\n2. **Nasr School**  \n   - Known for its strong emphasis on academics and extracurricular activities.\n\n3. **Slate \u2013 The School**  \n   - Offers a blend of traditional and modern teaching methods.\n\n---\n\n### **International Schools**\n1. **The Hyderabad Public School (HPS)**  \n   - One of the most prestigious schools in India, offering a well-rounded education.\n\n2. **Chirec International School**  \n   - Follows the IB and Cambridge curricula, with a focus on innovation and creativity.\n\n3. **Gitanjali School**  \n   - Known for its progressive teaching methods and emphasis on student development.\n\n---\n\n### **Factors to Consider**  \n- **Academic Focus**: Choose based on the board (CBSE, ICSE, State Board, or International) and the school\u2019s approach to academics.  \n- **Extracurricular Activities**: Look for schools that offer a variety of sports, arts, and clubs.  \n- **Facilities**: Check for modern infrastructure, labs, libraries, and sports facilities.  \n- **Location**: Consider proximity to your home to ensure convenience.  \n\nIt\u2019s advisable to visit the schools, interact with faculty, and assess the environment before making a decision.",
